 CROSS-SECTION EVALUATION PROCEDURE                               6622 1451
                                                                  6622 1451
 Adopted procedure is based on careful theoretical                6622 1451
 analysis utilizing available experimental data and               6622 1451
 nuclear reaction model calculations.                             6622 1451
                                                                  6622 1451
 This code integrates into a single system a number               6622 1451
 of important modules and features:                               6622 1451
                                                                  6622 1451
 - Spherical and deformed Optical Model including                 6622 1451
   coupled-channels code ECIS06 by J. Raynal                      6622 1451
 - Soft-rotator deformed Optical Model including                  6622 1451
   coupled-channels code OPTMAN by E.Soukhovitskii                6622 1451
   and coworkers                                                  6622 1451
 - Hauser-Feshbach statistical model including                    6622 1451
   width fluctuation correction, and the                          6622 1451
   optical model for fission with partial damping                 6622 1451
 - Quantum-mechanical MSD TUL model (codes ORION &                6622 1451
   TRISTAN by H.Lenske), and MSC NVWY model                       6622 1451
 - Exciton model with Iwamoto-Harada cluster                      6622 1451
   emission and Kalbach systematic angular distr.                 6622 1451
   (code PCROSS by R.Capote et al)                                6622 1451
 - Hybrid Monte Carlo preequilibrium model(M.Blann)               6622 1451
   (code DDHMS by M.Chadwick, mod. by B.V.Carlson)                6622 1451
 - Complete gamma-ray cascade after emission of                   6622 1451
   each particle, including realistic treatment of                6622 1451
   discrete transitions                                           6622 1451
 - Access to OM segment of the RIPL library [RIPL]                6622 1451
 - Built-in input parameter files, such as masses,                6622 1451
   level density, discrete levels, fission barriers               6622 1451
   and gamma strength functions based on the RIPL                 6622 1451
   library [RIPL]                                                 6622 1451
 - Automatic retrieval of experimental data from the              6622 1451
   EXFOR library                                                  6622 1451
 - ENDF-6 formatting (code EMPEND by A.Trkov)                     6622 1451
   coupled to graphical presentation capabilities                 6622 1451
   (code ZVView by V. Zerkin) through the chain of                6622 1451
   PrePro codes by D. Cullen                                      6622 1451
 - ENDF checking codes (CHECKR, FIZCON, PSYCHE)                   6622 1451
 - Highly automated fitting of optical model                      6622 1451
   parameters (by B.V. Carlson)                                   6622 1451
 - KALMAN code for fitting experimental data and                  6622 1451
 - generating covariances                                         6622 1451
 - Support for NJOY                                               6622 1451
